<subSubSection id="C37F6542FF85ED572BC9F893FEEDFEBF" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF85ED512BC9F893FBCFF876" blockId="19.[151,1436,1832,2019]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF85ED512BC9F893FEB5F8D7" bold="true" box="[198,269,1832,1858]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Male.</emphasis>
Body length, 9.0–10.0 mm. Wing length, 
<quantity id="4C9D9B2CFF85ED512814F892FC08F8D6" box="[795,944,1833,1859]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="6.2" valueMin="5.8">5.8–6.2 mm</quantity>
. General color brownish gray. Eyes and ocelli brownish yellow, facets homogenous, ocellar tubercle gray. Gena gray, clypeus bare and brown. Antenna brownish yellow arista darker; scape bare, half the length of pedicel; pedicel approximately oval; first flagellomere oval, as long as pedicel (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF85ED512988F81AFD45F82E" box="[647,765,1953,1979]" captionStart="FIGURES 57 – 60" captionStartId="20.[151,269,1431,1455]" captionTargetBox="[150,1409,194,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[133,1454,194,1407]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 57 – 60. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 57 — Wing, 58 — Antenna, 59 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 60 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177244/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF85ED5129D2F81AFD45F82E" box="[733,765,1953,1979]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="58.0">58</number>
</figureCitation>
), with many golden setae. Maxillary palpus long, slender (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF85ED512B90F872FEADF876" box="[159,277,1993,2019]" captionStart="FIGURES 57 – 60" captionStartId="20.[151,269,1431,1455]" captionTargetBox="[150,1409,194,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[133,1454,194,1407]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 57 – 60. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 57 — Wing, 58 — Antenna, 59 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 60 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177244/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF85ED512BFBF872FEADF876" box="[244,277,1993,2019]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="59.0">59</number>
</figureCitation>
). Proboscis and labella brownish to yellow. Occiput gray, with dark setae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1A6641FF82ED562B98FA2CFD9CFA44" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177244/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" targetBox="[150,1409,194,1406]" targetPageId="20">
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF82ED562B98FA2CFD9CFA44" blockId="20.[151,1436,1431,1489]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF82ED562B98FA2CFEE7FA3A" bold="true" box="[151,351,1431,1455]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">FIGURES 57–60.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C654D4AFF82ED562A68FA23FDEEFA3A" box="[359,598,1432,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="camargoi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF82ED562A68FA23FDEEFA3A" box="[359,598,1432,1455]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="4C654D4AFF82ED562A68FA23FE50FA3A" box="[359,488,1432,1455]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" genus="Chrysopilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysopilus</taxonomicName>
camargoi
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B911EADBFF82ED562950FA2CFD25FA3A" bold="true" box="[607,669,1431,1455]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22257A0FF82ED562950FA2CFD25FA3A" box="[607,669,1431,1455]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male holotype: 57 — Wing, 58 — Antenna, 59 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 60 — Spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF82ED562BCAF9BEFF78F965" blockId="20.[151,1437,1541,2019]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Thorax dark brown, scutellum lighter than scutum, with many golden setae. Halter bare, knob yellowish, stem darker. Coxae brownish gray, femora and tibiae yellowish. Wing hyaline with antero-distal brownish macula (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF82ED562BF4F9EEFECAF9FA" box="[251,370,1621,1647]" captionStart="FIGURES 57 – 60" captionStartId="20.[151,269,1431,1455]" captionTargetBox="[150,1409,194,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[133,1454,194,1407]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 57 – 60. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 57 — Wing, 58 — Antenna, 59 — Maxillary palpus, female paratype: 60 — Spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177244/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF82ED562A5EF9EEFECAF9FA" box="[337,370,1621,1647]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="57.0">57</number>
</figureCitation>
); pterostigma rounded, large; areas around crossveins m-m and r-m pigmented; R 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF82ED562E3DF9DEFA82F9E6" box="[1330,1338,1637,1651]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF82ED562E4BF9DEFAF3F9E6" box="[1348,1355,1637,1651]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.0">3</number>
reaching C far from R 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF82ED562A6DF92BFED2F90B" box="[354,362,1680,1694]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
, with wide distal concavity; R 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF82ED5629D5F92BFD5AF90B" box="[730,738,1680,1694]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="4.0">4</number>
forking with almost right angle, without short appendage, with distal fold toward anterior margin; CuA 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF82ED5629AFF900FD10F95C" box="[672,680,1723,1737]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
and A 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF82ED5629FAF900FD45F95C" box="[757,765,1723,1737]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
fusing far from margin; crossvein m-m far from origin of M 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF82ED562BBEF95DFF01F961" box="[177,185,1766,1780]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA36C9FF82ED562BCAF8BAFDAAF82E" blockId="20.[151,1437,1541,2019]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Abdomen brownish gray, with golden setae on tergites. Gonocoxite and gonostylus brown; gonocoxite longer than wide; gonostylus long, slightly rounded distally, covered with long setae, a group of fine setae medially; aedeagus long; ejaculatory and gonocoxal apodemes relatively short, gonocoxal apodeme curved outwards; lateral ejaculatory process wide, curved inward (
<figureCitation id="135E2A4CFF82ED562850F8C2FC60F806" box="[863,984,1913,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 61 – 65" captionStartId="21.[151,269,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[181,1403,474,1879]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[181,1406,474,1880]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 61 – 65. Chrysopilus camargoi sp. n., male holotype: 61 — Terminalia, dorsal view, 62 — Terminalia, dorsal view, female paratype: 63 — Terminalia, ventral view, 64 — Sternite VIII, ventral view, 65 — Genital fork (S IX)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/177245/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figure 
<number id="3DAD24EEFF82ED5628B7F8C2FC60F806" box="[952,984,1913,1939]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="61.0">61</number>
</figureCitation>
); meso-anterior incision of tergite IX short (
